  "prompt": "I do not have a surname on passport or any of my education certificates. What should be the most appropriate step now to fix the issue?",
  "response": "To resolve this issue, you can take the following steps:\n\n1. Legal Name Change:\n- Obtain an affidavit from a local court or magistrate\n- Create a deed poll to officially add a surname\n- This document can be used to update all your official records\n\n2. Documentation Process:\n- Get an affidavit stating the reason for not having a surname\n- Prepare supporting documents like birth certificate\n- Gather educational certificates and passport copies\n\n3. Government Procedures:\n- Visit your local revenue/municipal office\n- Apply for surname addition\n- Submit required documents\n- Pay necessary fees\n\n4. Passport Update:\n- Apply for passport re-issuance with new surname\n- Submit court affidavit and other supporting documents\n- Follow passport office guidelines\n\n5. Educational Certificates:\n- Contact respective educational institutions\n- Request certificate correction/reissuance\n- Provide legal documents supporting surname addition\n\n6. Recommended Additional Steps:\n- Consult a local lawyer for proper guidance\n- Seek advice from regional authorities\n- Maintain consistent documentation across platforms\n\nThe specific process might vary slightly depending on your location and local regulations. Consulting local authorities directly would provide the most accurate guidance.",
